# Constitution

Hard rules for this Playwright suite. Details live in `@playwright-convention` and `@qa-mission`; this is the checklist read every task.

## MUST

| Rule | Why |
|------|-----|
| **Role-based locators** (`getByRole` → label → text → testid) | Tests track what users and assistive tech see |
| **Web-first assertions** (`expect(locator)…`) | Wait on state, not arbitrary time |
| **`storageState` auth** (setup project) | Fast, stable login; no inline credentials |
| **Unique self-cleaning data** (`Date.now()` / Faker + API teardown) | No collisions; no leftover records |
| **Layered strategy tags** — always `@regression`; add `@smoke`, `@sanity`, `@api`, or `@destructive` as needed (not on `describe`) | Regression = full suite; smoke/sanity = CI slices |

## SHOULD

| Practice | When |
|----------|------|
| **Faker factories** | Any generated name, email, or payload |
| **Enums for repeated strings** | Status labels, routes, roles used in 2+ places |
| **JSDoc on POM action methods** | Non-obvious flows, params, or side effects |

## WON'T

| Never | Route instead |
|-------|---------------|
| **XPath** | Re-discover via role/label/text/testid |
| **`waitForTimeout`** | Web-first `expect` or action auto-wait |
| **Hardcoded secrets** | `process.env` + setup-project auth |
| **TypeScript `any`** | Proper types or `unknown` + narrowing |
| **Weakened assertions** | `@qa-mission` — human gate before any change |
| **Heal a real app bug** | `@triage` → `@bug-reporter` after human approval |
| **Tags on `describe`** | Tag individual `test()` blocks only |

## Agent governance

Behavioral contract (not hook-enforced). Complements `@qa-mission` human gates.

### Audit-then-edit

1. **Audit** — read the relevant files, CI, AC, or live UI before changing anything.
2. **Propose** — emit a Proposal block (below) for every non-trivial task.
3. **Edit** — only after the confidence gate allows it.

Trivial = typo, one-line rename the human named, or an already-approved patch. Everything else needs a Proposal first.

### Proposal (before edits)

```
## Proposal
Scope: <files / tests / flows touched>
Confidence: <1–10>
Rationale: <why this approach>
Unknowns: <gaps, or "none">
```

### Confidence gate

| Confidence | Action |
|------------|--------|
| **Below 5** | **Do not proceed.** Ask for the missing input (path, enum, env, credential, message, AC). |
| **5–7** | Proceed only with **explicit Unknowns** listed and **human approval**. |
| **8 or above** | Proceed. Still audit first; still do not invent values. |

### Never invent

Do not invent a **path**, **enum**, **env var**, **credential**, or **user-facing message**. Ask the human or explore (repo search, browser a11y snapshot, Jira AC) instead.

## Skills & agents

**Skills:** `explore-and-generate` — gap discovery without a ticket; `self-heal` — POM locator repair after UI drift (test issue only).

**Agents:** `triage` — classify red CI; `test-writer` — plan → spec; `bug-reporter` — Jira filing after human approval.
